treet patrolmen, military officers and legislators, clergy and prostitutes, business owners and shantytown residents—to present a vivid account of politics on the ground. Her in-depth comparative analysis reveals surprising parallels in the reform patterns adopted in Argentina and Brazil in the past decade, supporting conclusions that carry disturbing implications for the prospects for democratic consolidation in Latin America as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCivil societyxArgentina. 0aCivil societyxBrazil. 0aCivil societyzArgentina. 0aCivil societyzBrazil. 0aCrimexArgentina. 0aCrimexBrazil. 0aCrimezArgentina. 0aCrimezBrazil. 0aCriminalitéxArgentine. 0aCriminalitéxBrésil. 0aDemocratizationxLatin America. 0aDemocratizationzLatin America. 0aDémocratisationxAmérique latinexArgentinaxBrazilxLatin AmericaxArgentinienxPolizeixKriminalitätxRechtsstaatxBrasilienxPolizeixKriminalitätxRechtsstaatxArgentinienxBrasilien. 0aPolicexArgentina. 0aPolicexArgentine. 0aPolicexBrazil. 0aPolicexBrésil. 0aPolicezArgentina. 0aPolicezBrazil. 0aSociété civilexArgentine. 0aSociété civilexBrésil. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh1 aHinton, Mercedes S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978162637143940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781626371439423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781626371439/original  a978-3-11-078425-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV